        rationale: "The triad of progressive dysmenorrhea unresponsive to NSAIDs, deep dyspareunia, and infertility in a reproductive-age woman is classic for endometriosis. Fibroids typically cause menorrhagia rather than dysmenorrhea, PID presents acutely with fever, and ovarian torsion presents with acute unilateral pain."
